Description: Body sherd of East Greek grey ware large pottery vessel, probably a krater or dinos; dark grey fabric core sandwiched between pale brown margins, with mica inclusions; worn dark slip and inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: The sherd may well belong to the same vessel as British Museum 1965,0930.406; 1965,0930.407; 1965,0930.408; 1965,0930.410.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.022)
